"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence from the Police and Crime Commissioner for Leicestershire [CST0076]&#xa0;&#xa0;\nThe following questions have been asked by Public Administration Select Committee.\n&#xa0;\n•\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nWhat, if any, targets do you set for your police force?\n•\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nWhat impact do you think this has on police recording crime practices?\n•\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nHow do you assure yourself that the recorded crime figures for your area are correct?\n•\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nTo what extent can you trust the crime statistics for your area?\n&#xa0;\nTaking each in turn:\n&#xa0;\nWhat, if any, targets do you set for your police force?The \nPolice and Crime Plan 2013-2017 Executive Summary\n lists the targets that have been set for the 2013/14 Financial Year.\n&#xa0;\nWhat impact do you think this has on police recording crime practices?The setting of targets has no impact on police recording crime practices in Leicestershire, HMIC have reaffirmed this in their most recent inspections of Crime Recording Standards in the Force area.\n&#xa0;\nHow do you assure yourself that the recorded crime figures for your area are correct?The key reassurances are:\n&#xa0;\nTo what extent can you trust the crime statistics for your area?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nJanuary 2014\n&#xa0;\n"